This reverts commit 9e1477faa48148ad5b2c3664375a3520d589eb94.

Dev release commits must NOT be integrated with `master` -  they are intended to live in their own branches only. This is intentional and `master` should always be kept in `0.1.0.dev0` until we move into "real" (non dev) releases.

@bmw, did you pull this in as a part of m request in #926?

- /arlas/explore/{collection}/_opensearch moves to /arlas/ogc/opensearch/{collection}
- /arlas/wfs/{collection} moves to /arlas/ogc/wfs/{collection}
- /arlas/collections/csw moves to /arlas/ogc/csw/
- /arlas/collections/csw/_opensearch moves to /arlas/ogc/csw/opensearch

This fixes the Mercury Driver to work with the new parameters class 


@alexcjohnson This relied on being able to set what is essentially MultiParameters. 
Is there a particular reason why that is not allowed

Added support for using a surrogate vgg16 model. User should be able to use a pretrained vgg16 model, just as they could use resnet, or inception.

I feel like this would be useful because many articles have been published that use the feature extraction features of VGG-16 for other analysis such as image segmentation, multi-label classifications etc. Thus, this would be a useful thing to have.

@yanneta @jph00
